textMap.PRIMARY: Bonus Content: This episode of "The Man in the High Castle" is one of a number of titles that benefit from exclusive videos and behind-the-scenes photos, accessible in the X-Ray Bonus tab in Prime Video.
The GNR is not technically an occupied nation as it has an independent American Nazi government administrated by American Nazi citizens under the supervision of Berlin, the seat of global Nazi power.

In our history, Hitler's unification plan for Aryan nations was to promote assimilation over occupation. This ideology is carried out in the portrayal of Nazi government and society in "The Man in The High Castle."

In Juliana's vision, she sees a sign for the Lackawanna Coal Mine. The mine, which was established in 1860 is located in Scranton, Pennsylvania and was eventually shut down over 100 years later, in 1966.
In Philip K. Dick's book, Juliana begins a relationship with a man she believes is an Italian veteran named Joe Cinnadella.
In our history, the Ahnenerbe was an SS research institute, founded by Heinrich Himmler in 1935. Its research was focused on supporting the supremacist ideology of the Reich.
The scientific concept at the center of "The Man in the High Castle" is known as the Many-Worlds Interpretation of quantum mechanics.

Executive producer Kalen Egan has said that Kido's story is an immigrant story, where Kido is an unintentional immigrant. He begins an assimilation process in America regardless of his attitude about the place.

The Japanese Navy is considered the most elite of the Empire's two military branches. It is more technologically advanced and was a key actor in the Pacific offensives that ultimately led to victory in Japan's conquest of the American West.
In the alt history, all religion is banned in the Reich. The Christian bible and, indeed, any religious text or object is seen as a symbol of resistance.

"The Man in the High Castle" is essentially set in a cold war era. Both Japan and the Reich are nuclear powers, so Berlin has to use different modes of dominance over Japan. The Japanese Empire is at a disadvantage with the Reich strangling access to oil.

In real-world history, famed fashion designer Coco Chanel was the one-time lover of Baron Hans Gnther von Dincklage from 1940 to 1950. Von Dincklage was a representative of the Reich Ministry of Popular Enlightenment and Propaganda.

George Lincoln Rockwell is the Reichsmarshall of America in Season 3 of "The Man in the High Castle" but, in real-world history, he was the post-war leader of the American Nazi Party, founded in Arlington, Virginia in 1959.

The Japanese Empire tolerates homosexuality if it is inconspicuous but there are no laws banning it. In the American Reich, homosexuality - especially between men - is an offense that could be punishable by death in many instances.
